    "content": "<p>2\ufe0f\u20e36\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 26th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>If you ever put together a systemd service, you must be aware of the ExecStart= setting, which declares the command line to actually invoke for the service. It&#39;s probably *the* most important setting of all.</p><p>ExecStart= has various features these days. Besides specifier expansion and a limited form of environment variable expansion, ...</p>",
