      "content": "<p>\u2026 configured in User= of the same service). Or in other words: we invoke the shell and pass the specified command via the &quot;-c&quot; parameter to it.</p><p>What&#39;s this good for? Of course, you could use this for embedding shell scripts into the sevice file, but I am not sure that would be too wise (since which shell is used is configured in the user record, not in the service, i.e. you might end up writing a zsh script that will be interpreted by bash or similar).</p>",
